Commentary Text: Siraj to Starc, out Caught by Shreyas Iyer!! Another good catch and Australia have been bowled out for 199. The slower ball is dug into the pitch, Starc hangs back to pull but gets it high on the bat, the ball is in the air for a long time, Shreyas runs in from deep square leg and judges it well to take it after that sprint. India need exactly 200 to win this. Starc c Shreyas Iyer b Siraj 28(35) [4s-2 6s-1]

Commentary Text: Kuldeep Yadav to Maxwell, out Bowled!! The move to bring back Kuldeep Yadav has worked wonders. The leg-stump is flattened and Maxwell is disappointed as he misses the pull. Rohit celebrates with a smile. A fast leggie that hastens off the pitch, the length is not short to pull, Maxwell makes that error and misses, rushes past the shot and knocks over leg-stump. Another massive wicket for Maxwell could have potentially played a match-winning knock. Maxwell b Kuldeep Yadav 15(25) [4s-1]

Commentary Text: Jadeja to Carey, out Lbw!! Two in the over and Australia in trouble now. Carey took long to decide whether to review or not, the time has run out and he has to walk back. Stump-to-stump, fullish on middle and leg, Carey's bat is in an awkward tangle around the front pad as he tries to work around the corner, the bat hits the pad and the ball turns in to thud into the pad. Loud appeal and umpire Richard Kettleborough had the finger up after a good thought. Hawk-Eye shows it to be crashing into the top of the stumps. Three reds and even a review wouldn't have helped. Kohli with a smile points at Rohit - suggesting as if the plan worked. Carey lbw b Jadeja 0(2)

Commentary Text: Jadeja to Labuschagne, out Caught by Rahul!! Clear edge and the review is wasted. Full and just outside off, Labuschagne went for big slogsweep as he went down on his knee, healthy top-edge and Rahul takes a sharp catch. Not an easy catch but went straight into the middle of the glove. Labuschagne walks off shaking his head. He knew there was an edge, so why did he take the review? Two quick wickets for Jadeja and India on top as the players take an official drinks break. Labuschagne c Rahul b Jadeja 27(41) [4s-1]

Commentary Text: Jadeja to Smith, out Bowled!! What a ball. First ball after a lengthier break, Jadeja strikes. This is unplayable. Drift in and towards leg-stump, or even just outside the leg-stump, on a good length, then as it lands, it rips right across Smith's forward defence, went a long way and clips the top of off-stump. Smith can only acknowledge the greatness of that delivery with a wry smile. He knows he did not have a chance with that one. Another set batter dismissed just when he was looking dangerous. Smith b Jadeja 46(71) [4s-5]

Commentary Text: Cummins to Rahul, SIX, India win by 6 wickets. Rahul is down on his haunches in shock. He was surprised by the timing on that, he wanted this to be a four so he could then hit a six to reach his hundred, but the timing was so good that the ball travels all the way denying him a possible shot at a three-figure score. The lights have gone off at Chepauk and some kind of disco lights are being played. It really is a party atmosphere in Chennai. Full delivery outside off, Rahul had the width to free his hands and he smokes it over extra cover, struck it better than he wanted but it does the job for India

Commentary Text: Hazlewood to Kohli, out Caught by Labuschagne!! The partnership is broken. But it might be too late for Australia. Kohli walks off to a standing ovation. He has put India in the driver's seat. This was the short ball banged into the wicket, Kohli takes it on and does not keep the pull down, struck straight to mid-wicket and Marnus reacts to take a sharp catch. Commentary Text: Hazlewood to Shreyas Iyer, out Caught by Warner!! Oh dear me!! 2-3, nope this isn't a football score... Commentary Text: Hazlewood to Rohit, out Lbw!! How big a blow is that? A big inswinger from Hazlewood, bowled from a fuller length, cuts in sharply after pitching. Think that Hardik Pandya ball to Babar Azam. But this ball was much straighter and the inward movement catches Rohit playing the wrong line. Struck in front of middle and ball tracking confirms it would have clipped leg stump. For once, Chepauk is silenced by a yellow team taking early wickets. Rohit lbw b Hazlewood 0(6)
